Step 1. Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.  
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 5,718,450.67 and Total Revenue = 20,318,450.67.  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (5,718,450.67 / 20,318,450.67) × 100  
  ≈ 0.2815 × 100  
  ≈ 28.15%

Step 2. Calculate the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio.  
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –18,924,462.44.  
• From the balance sheet, Total Liabilities is taken as the sum of Accounts Payable and Taxes Payable. Here, Accounts Payable = 0.00 and Taxes Payable = 1,015,922.54 so Total Liabilities = 1,015,922.54.  
• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Liabilities)  
  = (–18,924,462.44) / (1,015,922.54)  
  ≈ –18.63

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "28.15%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-18.63"
  }
}
